abstract: Nothing is loft to be added to what we pub lished yesterday about the burning of Congress all, except that the loss will not be far below 300,000, and the insurance reaches $134,750. abstract: MANHATTAN COLLEGE.--On Wednesday an examination of the higher classes of this institution took place in the presence of some gentlemen desirous of noting the progress of the College. The students were examined in mental philosophy, mathematics and the Greek and Latin Languages. The examination in philosophy, taking in metaphysics, logic and ethics, was conducted in Latin, and the young gentlemen spoke with great case and elegance.

abstract: A fire was discovered last evening between 7 and 8 o'clock in the grocery-store No. 13 Roosevelt street, kept by CHARLES JEHRING. The door having been forced in, it was found that some shavings were burning beneath the counter. Assistant Fire Marshal H. 0. BAKER made an investigation of the premises, which resulted in finding a quantity of kerosene oilamong tile shavings.

abstract: The steamer City of Memphis, from New Orleans to St. Louis, when near Huck's Island, 80 miles below this city, at 7 o'clock this morning ex ploded one or both boilers, which carried away about 60 feet of the cabin and upper works, with the pilot house and the people in that portion of the boat. Thenumber of lives lost is estimated at from 40 to 60.

abstract: The naval receiving-ship New-Hampshire, in tow of the supply-ship Newbern, arrived this forenoon. The former vessel anchored in the stream, where the will remain until Monday next, when she goes to Gosport Navy-yard to relieve the Constellation. The Newbern sailed directly for New-York. The double-ender naval steamer Winnepec, which for several weeks past has been undergoing repairs at the Navy-yard, sailed to-day.

abstract: STOPPING A PRIZE FIGHT.--Information was received at the West Philadelphia Station-house, on Saturday afternoon, that a prize mill would be fought on Sunday. Lieut. TOLBERT, with twenty-policemen, watched the outskirts of the ward until 4 o'clock in the afternoon. Then they ascertained that the fight was in progress at Gray's Works, on the Darby road, near the Media Railroad intersection. The detachment reached the grove just as the mill was commencing. It was hurriedly postponed.

abstract: The new steamer Grampus was launched from the ship-yard of JEREMIAH SIMONSON, Esq., at 9:30 o'clock yesterday morning, in the presence of a large concourse of spectators. abstract: SUICIDE OF A COLORED SAILOR.--HENRY A. LEWIS, a colored seaman, 54 years of age, committed suicide at the house of MARGARET SENETER, No. 24 First-street, yesterday forenoon, by swallowing about an ounce and a half of laudanum. It appears, from the account of the woman at whose house he boarded, that LEWIS came home on Saturday somewhat in liquor, and with a bottle of medicine, which, discovering to be laudanum, she took away from him.

abstract: AN UNUSUAL STREET SCENE.--About noon yesterday an unusal scene was witnessed on Walnutstreet, above Third. A broker, who has his office in that immediate neighborhood, was met by a young woman, who proceeded to apply a cowhide to him shoulders.
